Key Match Events: Yordan Alvarez homered and Kyle Tucker added two RBIs to give him an American League-leading 101
The Astros scored five runs in the fifth to take a 7-4 lead
Tucker’s two-run double put the Astros on top
Ryan Pressly struck out Manny Machado and Xander Bogaerts to end the threat and get his 30th save
Post-Match Reflections: The Astros increased their lead over the Mariners in the AL West to 1 1/2 games
It’s the second consecutive 100-RBI season for Tucker
Miscellaneous Highlights: Jurickson Profar had three hits, highlighted by a two-run homer
Luis Campusano added two hits and an RBI
The Astros went to their bullpen early after starter Cristian Javier allowed four hits and four runs in just four innings
San Diego’s Seth Lugo (6-7) gave up seven hits and six runs in 4 1/3 innings
